FBIS4-60181 "drnes099_j_94008" FBIS-NES-94-099 Daily Report 21 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Southern Yemen To Announce Secession From North Southern Yemen To Announce Secession From North Envoy Comments JN2105190694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 1745 GMT 21 May 94 JN2105190694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Foreign Minister Muhammad Salim Basindwah this morning received his excellency the Russian Federation's ambassador. The ambassador stressed that the Russian Federation has supported Yemeni unity since its proclamation, for it embodies the ambitions of all Yemeni political and social forces and translates their aspirations for consolidating democratic values and (?professional) liberties. He said that the Russian Federation believed and continues to believe that constructive dialogue and political advancement within the framework of political pluralism is the ideal approach for bolstering Yemen's sovereignty and its international reputation. He said this approach is the best solution to all social and economic problems facing Yemen. He said that not on any level has Moscow considered the possibility of recognizing the new state in southern Yemen.
